<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-25"><hi rend="italic">October 25,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The Royal Government of Italy having accepted the first propositions
                                made by M. Delcassé, and the powers being in accord as to principal
                                points of the proposition, the minister of the King at Pekin has
                                been authorized to send to the Chinese plenipotentiaries an identic
                                note as soon as his colleagues shall have received from their
                                respective governments similar authorization.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">japan.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>